documents.t: tip This documentation outlines everything there is to know about FPSMath. If you're new to FPSMath, we suggest you follow this guide by clicking "Next" at the bottom of the page when you're done reading!
FPSmath is a simple Discord bot powered by Discord.js designed to convert video game sensitivities, fovs, mouse feel across themselves and preset games
FPSMath is the only calculation bot for everything to do with video game calculations Has a lot of games supported Under Construction Coming Soon!

For commands that accept input, you'll see keys with the following: <required> - parameters between <> must be included with the command [optional] - parameters between [] are optional parameters and may be excluded a | or | b - | means that you can use the parameters on either side of the symbol repeat... - means that you can provide multiple parameters as input These may be nested. Example: [parameter1 <parameter2>] means that the input is optional, but if you provide parameter1 then parameter2 is required. [parameter...] means that input is optional, and that the input can be any number of parameters.

Converts sensitivity to arcmin Usage# /arcmin <sens> <game | yaw> <cpi> Copy Supported Flags# -dp <output decimal places> Copy Examples# Anima04/11/2021 /arcmin 4 r6 800 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, 0.30558 arcmin Anima04/11/2021 /arcmin 2 0.032 800 -dp 8 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, 0.85333333 arcmin

Converts Sensitivity to cm/rev(cm/360) Usage# /cm <sens> <game | yaw> <cpi> Copy Supported Flags# -dp <output decimal places> Copy Examples# Anima04/11/2021 /cm 3 ow 1600 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, 28.86 cm/rev Anima04/11/2021 /cm 2 0.022 800 -dp 8 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, 25.97727273 cm/rev Aliases# cm/rev, cm/360 Copy

Converts Sensitivity to deg/mm Usage# /deg <sens> <game | yaw> <cpi> Copy Supported Flags# -dp <output decimal places> Copy Examples# Anima04/11/2021 /deg 3 ow 1600 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, 1.24724 deg/mm Anima04/11/2021 /deg 2 0.022 800 -dp 8 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, 1.38582677 deg/mm Aliases# deg/mm Copy

Converts Sensitivity to mpi(mrad/inch) Usage# /mpi <sens> <game | yaw> <cpi> Copy Supported Flags# -dp <output decimal places> Copy Examples# Anima04/11/2021 /mpi 3 ow 1600 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, 1.24724 mpi Anima04/11/2021 /mpi 2 0.022 800 -dp 8 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, 1.38582677 mpi Aliases# mrad, milliradian, mrad/inch, milliradian/inch Copy

Converts sensitivity to inch/rev(inch/360) Usage# /inch <sens> <game | yaw> <cpi> Copy Supported Flags# -dp <output decimal places> Copy Examples# Anima04/11/2021 /inch 3 ow 1600 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, 1.24724 inch/rev Anima04/11/2021 /inch 2 0.022 800 -dp 8 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, 1.38582677 inch/rev Aliases# inch/360, inch/rev Copy

Converts different sensitivities from one game or yaw value to another Usage# /convert <sens> <input game | yaw> <output game | yaw> Copy Supported Flags# -dp <output decimal places> Copy Examples# Anima04/11/2021 /convert 6 wz 0.022 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, 1.80000 Aliases# convert-sens, convertsens, convert-yaw, convertyaw Copy

Finds the true vertical and horizontal FOVs for certain aspect ratio that the game is being rendered at and game/FOV scaling method(FILM notation) To learn about FILM notation click here Usage# /fov <fov> <fov> <game name | FILM notation> <aspect ratio> Copy Supported Flags# -dp <output decimal places> Copy Examples# Anima04/11/2021 /fov 90 4ML3 16:19 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, Horizontal FOV: 64.551Vertical FOV: 73.740 Anima04/11/2021 /fov 103 ow 1920:1440 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, Horizontal FOV: 103.000Vertical FOV: 56.631 Aliases# fov-scaling, film, fovscailing Copy

Focal Length Scales a desired sensitivity between 2 fov values of the same type/ game Usage# /focal <sens> <old fov> <new fov> Copy Supported Flags# -dp <output decimal places> Copy Examples# Anima04/11/2021 /focal 0.95 90 100 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, 1.13217 Aliases# focal-scaling,focalscailing Copy

Converts cm/rev(default), deg/mm, inch/rev, mpi to a game sensitivity Usage# sens <cm/rev | deg/mm | inch/rev | mpi > <game | yaw> <cpi> Copy Supported Flags# -cm // if the input value's unit is cm/rev it is the default and optional -deg // if the input value's unit is deg/mm -inch // if the input value's unit is inch/rev -mpi // if the input value's unit is mpi Copy Examples# Anima04/11/2021 /sens 28.5 quake 1600 FPSMathBot04/11/2021 @Anima, 0.91148 Aliases# sens-cm, sens-deg, sens-inch, senscm, sensdeg, sensinch, sensmpi, sens-mpi Copy
tip Remember to use the bot prefix when running a command! You can also use @FPSMath instead of the server's prefix. Example @FPSMath help Below is a shortlist of all the bot commands.

Hint: You can click on a command to go to its full help entry. Command Description /arcmin Converts Sensitivity to arcmin /convert Converts Different Sensitivities from one game to another /cm Converts Sensitivity to cm/rev /deg Converts Sensitivity to deg/mm /mpi Converts Sensitivity to MPI /focal Focal Length Scales a desired sens between 2 fov values of the same type /fov Finds the true vertical and horizontal FOVs for certain aspect ratio and game/FOV scaling method(FILM notation) /inch Converts Sensitivity to inch/rev /sens Converts cm/rev|deg/mm|MPI|inch/rev to a game sensitivity default cm/rev

Command Description /help Displays a list of available commands, or detailed information for a specified command. /games Displays the supported games for this bot /getobject Displays the object from the array associated for a game /info Displays the major information about this bot /cminfo Displays an explanation for what cm/rev (cm/360) is
